650
01:00:39,333 --> 01:00:40,794
Something that came up I think

651
01:00:42,357 --> 01:00:55,533
Between all of us months ago, but also in conversations with private contractors, it's just that the fact that it was really hard to find places to put snow with this storm, I guess what

652
01:00:57,209 --> 01:01:01,111
What are our current snow storage and disposal constraints?

653
01:01:02,031 --> 01:01:05,652
What happens operationally when that capacity is maxed out?

654
01:01:05,892 --> 01:01:12,115
And are there any plans for, I mean, any kind of ideas about what we can do about that problem?

655
01:01:13,502 --> 01:01:14,563
I don't think we've maxed out yet.

656
01:01:14,823 --> 01:01:17,044
We have some locations for snow storage.

657
01:01:17,224 --> 01:01:21,627
The biggest hurdle for snow storage is the hauling, loading and hauling of the snow.

658
01:01:22,327 --> 01:01:23,648
It's not usually finding a location.

659
01:01:23,688 --> 01:01:24,288
We have a few.

660
01:01:24,728 --> 01:01:26,530
Wright's Pond is one of our main locations.

661
01:01:26,550 --> 01:01:27,810
So the parking lot, not the pond.

662
01:01:27,870 --> 01:01:28,611
We don't put it in the pond.

663
01:01:29,231 --> 01:01:30,112
We put it in the parking lot.

664
01:01:31,492 --> 01:01:32,593
And then there are others.

665
01:01:33,654 --> 01:01:39,357
We used, which we don't usually use, the high school practice field.

666
01:01:40,053 --> 01:01:43,394
This year, because we didn't have any place to put the snow that was there.

667
01:01:44,915 --> 01:01:46,376
So we get creative.

668
01:01:48,136 --> 01:01:56,680
But yeah, like I said, it's not necessarily the location, it's usually the hauling of the snow, we can haul it ourselves, it just takes a long time.

669
01:01:58,230 --> 01:02:01,592
If we decide to haul a street, then we're at that street all day hauling.

670
01:02:01,612 --> 01:02:02,693
We're not doing other things.

671
01:02:04,634 --> 01:02:09,857
And we will usually try to hire a contractor, so it frees us up to do other things usually.

672
01:02:10,578 --> 01:02:15,020
And it's a defined set of work that we can say, hey, contractor, go load and haul that spot.

673
01:02:17,082 --> 01:02:17,422
Awesome.

674
01:02:18,923 --> 01:02:19,864
Thanks.

675
